      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "- B\xE1nh Cu\u1ED1n is a Vietnamese dish made from steamed rice rolls
    filled with minced pork and mushrooms.\n\n- It is usually eaten for breakfast
    or a light meal.\n\n- The dish originated in Northern Vietnam and is commonly
    served with fried shallots and fish sauce.\n\n- Rice flour, wood ear mushrooms,
    and pork are the main ingredients."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f6b83f304dc3a98448bbbbe575dcc972, type: 2}
